text.tspan: *The best thing to use offline time for is
1) Be Druid offline until you have 2 days
2) Then be Faceless until you have 2 days
3) Then be Druid until you have 4-5 days
4) Then be Titan until you have 4-5 days
made by Cyden, data from the RG Discord
special thanks to Necrodoom, Curunur and Kiluh
*For R7+: All builds use elf bloodline
Ancient Device & Horn of the kings
5) Then be Merc until you have 11-12 days
glho kohhl snod, Need a Head Start?,
Beginning of R16, as any vanilla faction
End of R23: neutral research unlock
End of R29: prestige research unlock
If you don't have it yet
*R0-3 Elf: Use Angel if you have God's Rest

More of "Don't actively aim to get these early" rather than straight up "avoid getting these" as the rewards aren't worth the time spent getting them and/or there's simply more opportunistic times to get them in

the future, not because doing them early hurts your progress or anything. So it's perfectly fine if it comes to you naturally or you want to go for it early, it's just that it is not the most efficient use of your time if
you decide to get them earlier than we recommend you do and there's better things to spend your time on. Sounds convincing coming from an incremental games player.
*PS: The "I will unlock everything as soon as it comes" playstyle is not a very good playstyle to have.
